    $command += "            li { margin-bottom: 2px; }\n";
    $command += "        </style>\n";
    $command += "        <h2>Overview</h2>\n";
    $command += "        <div class=\"section\">\n";
    $command += "            <p>The <b>Inbetweener Tool</b> provides five slider modes for creating breakdowns\n";
    $command += "            and refining animation curves in Autodesk Maya. It works with <b>transforms, joints,\n";
    $command += "            NURBS curve controls</b>, and any object with keyable attributes.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <p>Version 2.1.0 &mdash; Pipeline Tools</p>\n";
    $command += "        </div>\n";
    $command += "\n";
    $command += "        <h2>Local Tweener (LT)</h2>\n";
    $command += "        <div class=\"section\">\n";
    $command += "            <p>Blends the current pose between the <b>previous</b> and <b>next</b> keyframes\n";
    $command += "            at the current time.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <ul>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">0%</span> = Previous keyframe pose</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">50%</span> = Halfway between (linear interpolation)</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">100%</span> = Next keyframe pose</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">Overshoot</span>: -50% to 150% for exaggerated motion</li>\n";
    $command += "            </ul>\n";
    $command += "            <p><b>Selection:</b> Select objects in the viewport, or select specific attributes\n";
    $command += "            via Graph Editor keyframes. Works with transforms, joints, and custom rig controls.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <p><b>Quick Buttons:</b> 1/8, 1/4, 1/2, 3/4, 7/8 and 0, 1/3, 2/3, 1 for precise\n";
    $command += "            common breakdown positions.</p>\n";
    $command += "        </div>\n";
    $command += "\n";
    $command += "        <h2>World Tweener (WT)</h2>\n";
    $command += "        <div class=\"section\">\n";
    $command += "            <p>Blends objects in <b>world space</b> using matrix interpolation with quaternion\n";
    $command += "            slerp for rotation. No viewport flickering.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <ul>\n";
    $command += "                <li>Range: <span class=\"key\">0%</span> to <span class=\"key\">100%</span> (no overshoot)</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li>Ideal for maintaining world-space arcs on constrained or parented controls</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li>Works with transforms and joints</li>\n";
    $command += "            </ul>\n";
    $command += "            <p><b>When to use:</b> When local-space tweening produces incorrect arcs due to\n";
    $command += "            parent space changes between keys (e.g., IK/FK switching, space-matched controls).</p>\n";
    $command += "        </div>\n";
    $command += "\n";
    $command += "        <h2>Blend to Neighbor (BN)</h2>\n";
    $command += "        <div class=\"section\">\n";
    $command += "            <p>Blends <b>selected Graph Editor keyframes</b> toward their neighboring keys.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <ul>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">&lt; 50</span>: Blend toward <b>previous</b> neighbor key</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">&gt; 50</span>: Blend toward <b>next</b> neighbor key</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">50</span>: No change (neutral)</li>\n";
    $command += "            </ul>\n";
    $command += "            <p><b>Selection:</b> Select controls in the viewport, or select keys in the Graph Editor.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <p><b>Use cases:</b> Smoothing motion, pulling timing toward holds, evening out spacing.</p>\n";
    $command += "        </div>\n";
    $command += "\n";
    $command += "        <h2>Blend to Default (BD)</h2>\n";
    $command += "        <div class=\"section\">\n";
    $command += "            <p>Blends selected controls from their <b>current values</b> toward the <b>rest pose</b>.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <ul>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">0</span>: Original values (no change)</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">100</span>: Default/rest pose</li>\n";
    $command += "            </ul>\n";
    $command += "            <p><b>Scan Default Pose:</b> Select your rig controls (or root) while in the\n";
    $command += "            default pose, then click &ldquo;Scan Default Pose&rdquo; to store accurate rest\n";
    $command += "            values. Without scanning, BD falls back to 0 for translate/rotate and 1 for scale.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <p><b>Selection:</b> Select controls in the viewport, or select keys in the Graph Editor.</p>\n";
    $command += "            <p><b>Use cases:</b> Zeroing out overshoot, resetting controls to neutral,\n";
    $command += "            reducing extreme poses.</p>\n";
    $command += "        </div>\n";
    $command += "\n";
    $command += "        <h2>Blend to Ease (BE)</h2>\n";
    $command += "        <div class=\"section\">\n";
    $command += "            <p>Calculates <b>cubic eased positions</b> and blends selected controls toward them\n";
