    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">Motion Trails</span>: Displays motion trail arcs for selected\n";
    $command += "                objects to visualize the animation path.</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">Overshoot Mode</span>: Extends Local Tweener range to\n";
    $command += "                -50% / 150% for exaggerated breakdown poses.</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li><span class=\"key\">Scan Default Pose</span>: Stores the current pose of selected\n";
    $command += "                controls as the rest/default pose for Blend-to-Default.</li>\n";
    $command += "            </ul>\n";
    $command += "        </div>\n";
    $command += "\n";
    $command += "        <h2>Tips &amp; Workflow</h2>\n";
    $command += "        <div class=\"section\">\n";
    $command += "            <ul>\n";
    $command += "                <li class=\"tip\">All slider operations are fully undoable with Ctrl+Z</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li class=\"tip\">All sliders work with both viewport selection and Graph Editor key selection</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li class=\"tip\">Sliders reset to neutral on release — the object stays at its tweened position</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li class=\"tip\">Constrained or expression-driven attributes are automatically skipped</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li class=\"tip\">Custom rig attributes (float, enum, etc.) are supported by LT if they have keyframes</li>\n";
    $command += "                <li class=\"tip\">Use Quick Buttons for precise mathematical breakdowns (thirds, quarters, eighths)</li>\n";
    $command += "            </ul>\n";
